# Metadata for chapter-11.md

## Provenance
- **Status:** POSTHUMOUS RECONSTRUCTION -- not written by Xavier O. Monasterio
- **Drafted:** 2026-07-04, with AI assistance (Claude), curated by Jorge Monasterio
- **No original source file exists.** Xavier's manuscript ends with chapter 8, whose final pages are working notes.

## Sources used for reconstruction
- FREI-APP (1993) -- antedating Frei's "eclipse" to the 12th-13th centuries; religious vs. non-religious narrative reading; inhabiting vs. imagining the biblical world; evidentialism
- chapter-8.md working notes -- the intellectualistic fallacy; Frei complement
- chapters 1-7 -- determinatio distrahens thesis, the resisters (de Hales, Kilwardby, Stephen of Tournai), Bonaventure's synthesis

## Classification
- **Type:** Reconstructed book manuscript chapter (chapter 11, conclusion of projected continuation)
- **Part of:** Unpublished book on philosophy of religion

## Notes
This concluding chapter attempts to complete the book's argument as Xavier outlined it
in his own notes and parallel essays, in his voice. It should not be quoted or cited as
his writing.
